     <div id="leaf-32" class="content box-no-title fluid-height headway-leaf">
      <div class="headway-leaf-inside">
       <div class="leaf-content">
        <div class="hentry page author-orvda category-news" id="post-87">
         <h1 class="page-title">
          Privacy Policy
         </h1>
         <div class="entry-content">
          <p>
           <strong>
            ONTARIO RECREATION VEHICLE DEALERS ASSOCIATION (ORVDA) PRIVACY POLICY AND THE PROTECTION OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Overview
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           The ORVDA continues to be committed to the protection of the private and personal information of our members as addressed in this Privacy Policy. To the best of our knowledge, our policy complies with the requirements of the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act of Canada.
          </p>
          <p>
           The Privacy Policy outlines our assurance to respect and protect our members’ personal information. We want to ensure that our members know the purpose for which this information is being collected, to whom this information may be disclosed, how the confidentiality of this information is protected, the steps needed to find out what personal information is recorded, and for how long we will retain this information.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            ORVDA Accountability
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           The ORVDA is responsible for our members’ personal information under our control. We have appointed a Privacy Officer who is accountable for ORVDA’s compliance to this Privacy Policy. Our information is protected by appropriate safeguards through technological measures such as passwords and/or encryption.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Purpose for Information Collection
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           The ORVDA makes every reasonable effort to make sure that an individual understands how her or his personal information will be used.
          </p>
          <p>
           Personal information is the information that relates to our members and their company, that identifies an individual as a member of the ORVDA, and that allows us to provide services and information directly to our members.
          </p>
          <p>
           We ask for personal information so that we can:
          </p>
          <ul>
           <li>
            Better understand and meet our members needs; and
           </li>
           <li>
            Inform our members about our member benefits and services, or those of our regional RVDA associations or partners, that we believe may be of interest to them.
           </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
           By joining Ontario Recreation Vehicle Dealers Association, an individual agrees to receive a membership kit and regular communications that will include offers from us as well as participating sponsors. From time to time, sponsors may also send separate communications to our members.
          </p>
          <p>
           Upon membership to the ORVDA, we may use names and addresses for general mailing purposes. We believe our members would also expect us to contact them to advise them of new and existing services that may be of interest to them. From time to time, we will inform our members of such services via direct marketing. Direct marketing material is usually delivered to them by mail, telephone or electronic means. A member may choose not to receive these offers and have their name deleted from our mailing lists.
          </p>
          <p>
           Upon membership, the individual also authorizes ORVDA to send personalized messages from time to time as well as our eBulletin and fax. These messages contain information about services offered by ORVDA and its partners that we think may be of interest to our members.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Consent
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           An individual’s knowledge and consent are necessary for the collection, use and disclosure of personal information. We only collect, use, or disclose personal information for purposes we believe would be considered appropriate under the circumstances.
          </p>
          <p>
           Of course, an individual may choose to only provide us with some or portions of their personal information. However, this choice may not enable us to provide them with the product, service, or information that has been requested or that could be offered to them.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Third-Party Disclosure
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           The names, addresses and telephone numbers of our members may be transmitted to a trusted third-party mailing service in order to inform them of products and services that we offer and that we believe may interest to them.
          </p>
          <p>
           Except as set out in this policy, or as required by law, ORVDA does not sell any personal information to any other organization and ORVDA will not transmit personal information to third parties without first obtaining written consent to do so. ORVDA may, however, disclose information in the following cases:
          </p>
          <ul>
           <li>
            to our lawyer;
           </li>
           <li>
            to a police force, if required by law;
           </li>
           <li>
            to a person authorized by a law or collective agreement;
           </li>
           <li>
            to a government agency which can oblige us to do so;
           </li>
           <li>
            in emergency situations in which the life, health or safety of a customer is in danger;
           </li>
           <li>
            to all other persons authorized by law;
           </li>
           <li>
            to an authorized contractor providing service to the individual;
           </li>
           <li>
            to another person for the development, enhancement, marketing or provision of any of ORVDA’s products or services on our behalf that we believe may be of interest to our members;
           </li>
           <li>
            to an agent retained by ORVDA in connection with the collection of the members’ account;
           </li>
           <li>
            to credit grantors and reporting agencies;
           </li>
           <li>
            to a person who, in the reasonable judgment of ORVDA, is seeking information as our members’ agent; or
           </li>
           <li>
            a third party or parties, where the member consents to such disclosure.
           </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Collection of Information
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           We only collect the information that we need in order to deliver services and information to our members. We do not use techniques to collect personal information about individuals without their knowledge. We do not use or disclose personal information for any purposes other than those for which it was collected, except with their consent or as required by law.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Information Retention
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           ORVDA retains information only as long as necessary for the fulfillment of services to its members and accordingly to legal requirement.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            ORVDA’s Responsibilities
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           Each of the association’s employees is responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of all personal information to which they have access. Our employees are kept informed about our policies and procedures for protecting personal information.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Policies &amp; Practices
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           We will make our complete policies and practices relating to the management of personal information readily available to our members.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Members’ Access to the Information
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           Upon request in writing, a member will be informed of the existence, use, and disclosure of personal information and will be given access to that information. We will assist any member who informs us that they need assistance in preparing a request concerning personal information. Members may challenge the accuracy and completeness of the information and have it amended as appropriate.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Accuracy
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           The information listed is believed to be accurate, complete and current when posted, but the ORVDA cannot guarantee that it will remain accurate or complete or that it will be current at all times. We will keep information as up-to-date as is necessary for the purposes for which it is to be used.
          </p>
          <p>
           Members may also view their profiles online through the association’s website at www.ontrvda.org. If a member wishes to review or verify the personal information in their file or find out to whom we have disclosed it, they can do so by writing to us at the following address.
          </p>
          <p>
           As well, any other questions about the ORVDA handling of personal information should be directed to the Privacy Officer.
          </p>
          <p>
           ORVDA Privacy Officer
           <br />
           P.O. Box 460
           <br />
           Harrow, ON N0R 1G0
           <br />
           or fax us at 519-738-0596
           <br />
           or e-mail us at aglabet@on.aibn.ca
          </p>
          <p>
           ORVDA thirty (30) days to reply to a request for access to a file.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Amendments
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           Members may ask to delete or correct any information contained in their file. The request for correction must be made by writing to us, either by mail at the above-mentioned mailing address, or by fax at the above-mentioned number, or by e-mail at the above-mentioned e-mail address. ORVDA has thirty (30) days to reply.
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Other Internet Related Policies
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           When members visit www.ontrvda.org without registering or otherwise interacting with the site, personal information and e-mail addresses are not recorded.
          </p>
          <p>
           ORVDA provides a number of services via www.ontrvda.org. To access these services, ORVDA may require members to identify themselves or provide personal information. We use the information provided to help us serve our members better. We will require personal information when members take part in surveys, or request information on the products and services offered by ORVDA.
          </p>
          <p>
           This policy discloses the privacy practices for our Web site. However, our site contains links to other sites. Once an individual links to another site, viewers are subject to the privacy and security policies of the new site. We encourage everyone to read the Privacy Policies of all Web sites visited, especially when sharing any personal information.
          </p>
          <p>
           1 This statement addresses the privacy policy of the Ontario Recreation Vehicle Dealers Association. The Ontario Recreation Vehicle Dealers Association (ORVDA) is a provincial association representing the interests of members and providing information and developing programs to enable the industry to realize its maximum potential.
          </p>
         </div>
